related_questions.question: How do I become an office assistant?
related_questions.snippet: A high school diploma or GED is the minimum educational requirement for office assistant positions. However, office assistants may have better job prospects with postsecondary training. Many vocational schools and community colleges offer office assistant certificates and administrative assistant associate's degrees.Dec 11, 2016

related_questions.question: What does an office clerk do?
related_questions.snippet: An office clerk is someone who typically works in an office doing a little bit of everything; answering phones, bookkeeping, filing, mailing, message delivery, data processing, running errands, sorting mail etc.
